# BACKTRANSLATION — The d=2048 SIC-POVM Moduli Construction: Structural Status

## Theorem (Macrocycle Closure and Its Obstruction)

The mathematical objects encoding the d=2048 SIC-POVM moduli construction — the ray class field K over Q(√(d(d-2))) with conductor (d)∞₁∞₂, the Zauner-symmetric SIC-POVM existence problem at dimension d, and the Connes embedding problem for type II₁ factors — admit a closed compositional cycle whose spectral invariants are dimension-independent (verified at d=12 and d=2048) but whose junction carries irreducible ambiguity: a two-site cross-link whose simultaneous binding on two conjugate axes is the structural address of the reduced character set problem.

---

## Lemma 1 (Flat Autocorrelation Reduction — Encoding)

The a=0 diagonal stratum of the SIC-POVM condition on d² equiangular vectors in ℂᵈ is equivalent to the real autocorrelation system

C₀ = Σ_k N_k² = 2/(d+1), C_m = 1/(d+1) for all m ≠ 0,

where N_k = |⟨ψ₀|ψ_k⟩|² are the diagonal overlaps. This equivalence holds by the Wiener-Khinchin identity: the discrete Fourier transform of the overlap vector recovers the autocorrelation, and inversion is exact on the SIC grid.

*Measured: validated on d=12 to residual below 10⁻⁵⁸ by direct computation. The reduction eliminates all phase information; the a=0 moduli are 1024 real quadratic constraints.*

**Structural role:** The demand — what the moduli must satisfy — is encoded losslessly as a system over the reals.

---

## Lemma 2 (Numerical Route Blocked — Boundedness)

The best Zauner-symmetric seed in the a=0 stratum at dimension d=2048 sits at a genuine local minimum with residual 3.9×10⁻³ and gradient norm 2.0×10⁻⁸. All local numerical methods (gradient descent, Newton, L-BFGS) are trapped.

*Measured: Proposition 3.1 of the manuscript. The minimum is certified by the Hessian spectrum at the seed.*

