## Proof of the Theorem

The five components of Lemma 1–6 form a closed apparatus: the demand (Lemma 1), the boundedness forcing algebraic construction (Lemma 2), the supply field (Lemma 3), its verified ascent (Lemma 4), the analytic route (Lemma 5), and the degeneracy-breaking mechanism (Lemma 6). Each is measured, each is closed.

The macrocycle (Lemma 7) closes among the three structural objects, with spectral radius ρ = 2.732 exceeding the bare cycle bound of 2 by exactly the contribution of the cross-link junction. The ring is branched, strained (σ = 0.292), and shaky — but it closes. The dimension independence (Lemma 8) confirms this is an architectural invariant, not an artifact of a specific dimension.

The direct path is blocked (Lemma 10): eight primitives are conflicted, the veracity class is aspirational, and the click test fails on ambiguity. The bridge passes through Connes (Lemma 9), not directly. The Belnap version does not participate in the ring (Lemma 11). The floor is too weak to identify the construction (Lemma 12).

The frontier is named (Lemma 13): the reduced character set computation, which selects from the 2²⁷ characters of the ray class group the specific orbits that carry the a=0 diagonal stratum. The a=0 moduli number 1024 = 2¹⁰, paired by Galois conjugation to 512 independent values, further constrained by the flat autocorrelation system to roughly 256 degrees of freedom. The character orbits carrying these moduli must be identifiable by their stabilizer under the Galois action that fixes the clock operator Z — a subgroup of index d = 2048 in the full group, halving the character count from 2²⁷ to 2¹⁶, then pairing to 2¹⁵. This gives 2¹⁵ = 32,768 candidate orbits, from which the autocorrelation constraints select the final set. The exact count and selection rule are not computed.

The ramified ascent (index 2²⁰ above the Hilbert class field) is needed if and only if the reduced character set lives outside the unramified part. This is testable on d = 12, where the full tower is small.

The unconditional existence of the SIC-POVM at d = 2048 — the Zauner node — remains the terminal open question. The explicit moduli, once constructed, would reduce it to two verifiable algebraic conditions: (i) the moduli N_k are nonnegative at the chosen embedding; (ii) the full SIC condition (all d² − 1 overlaps, not just the a=0 stratum) holds. Condition (i) is checkable once the moduli are explicit. Condition (ii) requires the phase strata (a ≠ 0), which are deferred.

---

## Conclusion

The d=2048 SIC-POVM moduli construction has verdict **B** (BOTH): the five proven components are **T** (established, measured, closed), the numerical route is **F** (provably blocked — the negation is established), the reduced character set is a genuine **B** (held dialetheia — simultaneously the key to completion and the current obstruction, a frontier to push), and the phase strata a ≠ 0 are **N** (not yet engaged, deferred). The macrocycle closes with strain and ambiguity at the junction. The title names the aim, not a completed casting. The vessel is cast; the gold is not yet poured.


