**Fact 3.** The dimension d=12 at which calibration was performed has d = disc(Q(√3)) = 12. This is the precise coincidence that makes d=12 the calibration dimension: the spectral radius of the ring lives in the quadratic field whose discriminant IS the calibration dimension.

These are real findings, grounded in tool output. They connect the ring's graph-theoretic spectrum to the algebraic number theory of the ray class field. The connection is: ρ ∈ Q(√3) ↔ Zauner order 3 ↔ discriminant 12 ↔ calibration dimension d=12.


